---
import Layout from '../../../layouts/Layout.astro';

const title = "Best Starting Classes Ranked - Elden Ring Guide";
const description = "Every Elden Ring starting class analyzed for melee, magic, and hybrid builds. Find the perfect starting class for your playstyle.";
---

<Layout {title} {description}>
  <article class="guide">
    <h1>🎓 Best Starting Classes Ranked</h1>

    <div class="intro">
      <p>Your starting class determines your initial stats, equipment, and playstyle. While you can respec later, choosing the right class saves hours of awkward early game. Here's every class ranked by viability for different builds.</p>
    </div>

    <section class="tier-list">
      <h2>🏆 Tier List Overview</h2>
      <table>
        <tr>
          <th>Tier</th>
          <th>Class</th>
          <th>Best For</th>
          <th>Difficulty</th>
        </tr>
        <tr class="tier-s">
          <td><strong>S</strong></td>
          <td>Samurai</td>
          <td>Melee, Dexterity builds</td>
          <td>⭐⭐ (Easy)</td>
        </tr>
        <tr class="tier-s">
          <td><strong>S</strong></td>
          <td>Astrologer</td>
          <td>Sorcery, Intelligence builds</td>
          <td>⭐⭐ (Easy)</td>
        </tr>
        <tr class="tier-a">
          <td><strong>A</strong></td>
          <td>Prophet</td>
          <td>Incantations, Faith builds</td>
          <td>⭐⭐⭐ (Medium)</td>
        </tr>
        <tr class="tier-a">
          <td><strong>A</strong></td>
          <td>Warrior</td>
          <td>Dual-wield, Dexterity builds</td>
          <td>⭐⭐⭐ (Medium)</td>
        </tr>
        <tr class="tier-b">
          <td><strong>B</strong></td>
          <td>Hero</td>
          <td>Strength builds, tank</td>
          <td>⭐⭐⭐ (Medium)</td>
        </tr>
        <tr class="tier-b">
          <td><strong>B</strong></td>
          <td>Bandit</td>
          <td>Arcane, bleed builds</td>
          <td>⭐⭐⭐ (Medium)</td>
        </tr>
        <tr class="tier-c">
          <td><strong>C</strong></td>
          <td>Vagabond</td>
          <td>Quality builds (Strength + Dexterity)</td>
          <td>⭐⭐⭐ (Medium)</td>
        </tr>
        <tr class="tier-c">
          <td><strong>C</strong></td>
          <td>Confessor</td>
          <td>Hybrid melee + Faith</td>
          <td>⭐⭐⭐ (Medium)</td>
        </tr>
        <tr class="tier-d">
          <td><strong>D</strong></td>
          <td>Prisoner</td>
          <td>Intelligence + Dexterity hybrid</td>
          <td>⭐⭐⭐⭐ (Hard)</td>
        </tr>
        <tr class="tier-d">
          <td><strong>D</strong></td>
          <td>Wretch</td>
          <td>Min-maxing, challenge runs</td>
          <td>⭐⭐⭐⭐⭐ (Very Hard)</td>
        </tr>
      </table>
    </section>

    <section class="detailed">
      <h2>📊 Detailed Class Analysis</h2>

      <div class="class-card">
        <h3>🥇 Samurai (Top Pick for Melee)</h3>
        <div class="stats-grid">
          <div class="stat"><strong>Level:</strong> 9</div>
          <div class="stat"><strong>Vigor:</strong> 12</div>
          <div class="stat"><strong>Mind:</strong> 11</div>
          <div class="stat"><strong>Endurance:</strong> 13</div>
          <div class="stat"><strong>Strength:</strong> 12</div>
          <div class="stat"><strong>Dexterity:</strong> 15</div>
          <div class="stat"><strong>Intelligence:</strong> 9</div>
          <div class="stat"><strong>Faith:</strong> 8</div>
          <div class="stat"><strong>Arcane:</strong> 11</div>
        </div>
        <p><strong>Starting Equipment:</strong> Uchigatana (katana), Longbow, Bloody Slash ash of war</p>
        <p><strong>Why S-Tier:</strong> The Uchigatana is one of the best early-game weapons. It causes bleed, has good range, and Bloody Slash is a powerful weapon skill. High Dexterity lets you use most dexterity weapons immediately.</p>
        <p><strong>Best For:</strong> Players who want a strong melee weapon from the start and plan to focus on Dexterity.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="class-card">
        <h3>🥇 Astrologer (Top Pick for Magic)</h3>
        <div class="stats-grid">
          <div class="stat"><strong>Level:</strong> 6</div>
          <div class="stat"><strong>Vigor:</strong> 9</div>
          <div class="stat"><strong>Mind:</strong> 15</div>
          <div class="stat"><strong>Endurance:</strong> 12</div>
          <div class="stat"><strong>Strength:</strong> 8</div>
          <div class="stat"><strong>Dexterity:</strong> 12</div>
          <div class="stat"><strong>Intelligence:</strong> 16</div>
          <div class="stat"><strong>Faith:</strong> 9</div>
          <div class="stat"><strong>Arcane:</strong> 7</div>
        </div>
        <p><strong>Starting Equipment:</strong> Glintstone Staff, Glintstone Pebble spell, Arc spell</p>
        <p><strong>Why S-Tier:</strong> 16 Intelligence is the highest starting Intelligence. You can use powerful sorceries immediately and have high Mind for FP. Glintstone Pebble is spammable and effective at range.</p>
        <p><strong>Best For:</strong> Players who prefer staying at range and using sorceries.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="class-card">
        <h3>🥈 Prophet (Best for Faith Builds)</h3>
        <div class="stats-grid">
          <div class="stat"><strong>Level:</strong> 7</div>
          <div class="stat"><strong>Vigor:</strong> 10</div>
          <div class="stat"><strong>Mind:</strong> 14</div>
          <div class="stat"><strong>Endurance:</strong> 10</div>
          <div class="stat"><strong>Strength:</strong> 11</div>
          <div class="stat"><strong>Dexterity:</strong> 10</div>
          <div class="stat"><strong>Intelligence:</strong> 7</div>
          <div class="stat"><strong>Faith:</strong> 16</div>
          <div class="stat"><strong>Arcane:</strong> 10</div>
        </div>
        <p><strong>Starting Equipment:</strong> Sacred Seal, Heal incantation, Catch Flame incantation</p>
        <p><strong>Why A-Tier:</strong> 16 Faith is the highest starting Faith. You get healing and fire magic, which are useful throughout the game. Faith builds are versatile and can use weapons with fire or lightning buffs.</p>
        <p><strong>Best For:</strong> Players who want a hybrid of melee and support magic.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="class-card">
        <h3>🥈 Warrior (Best for Dual-Wield)</h3>
        <div class="stats-grid">
          <div class="stat"><strong>Level:</strong> 8</div>
          <div class="stat"><strong>Vigor:</strong> 11</div>
          <div class="stat"><strong>Mind:</strong> 10</div>
          <div class="stat"><strong>Endurance:</strong> 11</div>
          <div class="stat"><strong>Strength:</strong> 10</div>
          <div class="stat"><strong>Dexterity:</strong> 16</div>
          <div class="stat"><strong>Intelligence:</strong> 10</div>
          <div class="stat"><strong>Faith:</strong> 8</div>
          <div class="stat"><strong>Arcane:</strong> 9</div>
        </div>
        <p><strong>Starting Equipment:</strong> Twinblade, Scimitar, Bloodstained Dagger</p>
        <p><strong>Why A-Tier:</strong> 16 Dexterity and starts with two weapons. The Twinblade has good range and damage, and you can dual-wield for higher DPS. High Dexterity lets you use most dex weapons early.</p>
        <p><strong>Best For:</strong> Players who like fast, aggressive melee combat.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="class-card">
        <h3>🥉 Hero (Best for Strength)</h3>
        <div class="stats-grid">
          <div class="stat"><strong>Level:</strong> 7</div>
          <div class="stat"><strong>Vigor:</strong> 14</div>
          <div class="stat"><strong>Mind:</strong> 9</div>
          <div class="stat"><strong>Endurance:</strong> 12</div>
          <div class="stat"><strong>Strength:</strong> 16</div>
          <div class="stat"><strong>Dexterity:</strong> 8</div>
          <div class="stat"><strong>Intelligence:</strong> 7</div>
          <div class="stat"><strong>Faith:</strong> 10</div>
          <div class="stat"><strong>Arcane:</strong> 11</div>
        </div>
        <p><strong>Starting Equipment:</strong> Battle Axe, Large Leather Shield, Reduvia (dagger)</p>
        <p><strong>Why B-Tier:</strong> 16 Strength is the highest starting Strength. High Vigor (14) gives good survivability. The Battle Axe hits hard but is slow. Good for players who want to tank hits and trade blows.</p>
        <p><strong>Best For:</strong> Players who prefer slow, heavy-hitting weapons and high survivability.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="class-card">
        <h3>⚠️ Wretch (Challenge Mode Only)</h3>
        <div class="stats-grid">
          <div class="stat"><strong>Level:</strong> 1</div>
          <div class="stat"><strong>Vigor:</strong> 10</div>
          <div class="stat"><strong>Mind:</strong> 10</div>
          <div class="stat"><strong>Endurance:</strong> 10</div>
          <div class="stat"><strong>Strength:</strong> 10</div>
          <div class="stat"><strong>Dexterity:</strong> 10</div>
          <div class="stat"><strong>Intelligence:</strong> 10</div>
          <div class="stat"><strong>Faith:</strong> 10</div>
          <div class="stat"><strong>Arcane:</strong> 10</div>
        </div>
        <p><strong>Starting Equipment:</strong> Club only</p>
        <p><strong>Why D-Tier:</strong> All stats are 10, which seems balanced but means you're weak at everything initially. The Club is terrible. You need to find better equipment immediately.</p>
        <p><strong>Best For:</strong> Experienced players who want to min-max their build or challenge themselves. Not recommended for first playthrough.</p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="recommendations">
      <h2>💡 Recommendations by Playstyle</h2>

      <div class="recommendation">
        <h3>🗡️ First Playthrough / Beginner</h3>
        <p><strong>Choose:</strong> Samurai or Vagabond</p>
        <p><strong>Why:</strong> Both have good starting equipment and balanced stats. Samurai's Uchigatana is excellent, and Vagabond has high Vigor for survivability.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="recommendation">
        <h3>🔮 Pure Magic User</h3>
        <p><strong>Choose:</strong> Astrologer (for sorcery) or Prophet (for incantations)</p>
        <p><strong>Why:</strong> Highest starting Intelligence or Faith. You can use powerful spells immediately without wasting points.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="recommendation">
        <h3>🩸 Bleed / Arcane Build</h3>
        <p><strong>Choose:</strong> Bandit or Samurai</p>
        <p><strong>Why:</strong> Bandit has high Arcane for bleed builds. Samurai's Uchigatana already causes bleed, and you can scale it with Arcane later.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="recommendation">
        <h3>🛡️ Tank / Heavy Armor</h3>
        <p><strong>Choose:</strong> Hero or Vagabond</p>
        <p><strong>Why:</strong> Both have high Vigor and Endurance for wearing heavy armor and wielding large weapons.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="recommendation">
        <h3>⚡ Hybrid Builds</h3>
        <p><strong>Choose:</strong> Confessor (melee + faith) or Prisoner (melee + sorcery)</p>
        <p><strong>Why:</strong> These classes start with balanced melee and magic stats, making hybrid builds easier to develop.</p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <div class="final-tip">
      <h2>🎯 Final Advice</h2>
      <p>Don't stress too much about your starting class. You can respec later using Larval Tears (found throughout the world). The most important thing is to pick a class that matches your preferred playstyle for the early game. You'll naturally evolve your build as you find better equipment and discover your preferences.</p>
      <p><strong>Remember:</strong> Vigor is the most important stat for all builds. Get it to 20-25 as soon as possible for survivability. Everything else can wait.</p>
    </div>
  </article>
</Layout>

<style>
  .guide {
    line-height: 1.8;
  }

  .intro {
    background: #f9f9f9;
    padding: 1.5rem;
    border-radius: 8px;
    margin-bottom: 2rem;
  }

  .tier-list table {
    margin: 1rem 0;
  }

  .tier-s {
    background: #fff3cd;
  }

  .tier-a {
    background: #d4edda;
  }

  .tier-b {
    background: #d1ecf1;
  }

  .tier-c {
    background: #f8d7da;
  }

  .tier-d {
    background: #e2e3e5;
  }

  .class-card {
    background: #f9f9f9;
    padding: 1.5rem;
    border-radius: 8px;
    margin: 1.5rem 0;
    border-left: 4px solid #c41e3a;
  }

  .stats-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(120px, 1fr));
    gap: 0.5rem;
    margin: 1rem 0;
    background: white;
    padding: 1rem;
    border-radius: 6px;
  }

  .stat {
    padding: 0.5rem;
    background: #f0f0f0;
    border-radius: 4px;
    text-align: center;
  }

  .recommendation {
    background: #f9f9f9;
    padding: 1.5rem;
    border-radius: 8px;
    margin: 1.5rem 0;
    border-left: 4px solid #28a745;
  }

  .final-tip {
    background: linear-gradient(135deg, #1a1a2e 0%, #16213e 100%);
    color: white;
    padding: 2rem;
    border-radius: 12px;
    margin-top: 3rem;
  }

  .final-tip h2 {
    color: #ffd700;
    border: none;
  }
</style>
